args: *pant* I somehow managed...to take\none down! How many does that leave?
One, two, three—oh crap, so many!\nBut I can't give up, no matter what.
You're tellin' me Farren marched into a\nSyndicate base?!
Yes. You two were kind enough to rescue\nus, but that wasn't everyone, I'm afraid.
All the young, healthy men seem to have\nbeen taken someplace else.
I see. They musta brought people who'd be\neasy to experiment on to the base first.\nAnd Farren went after 'em, y'say?
Yes. He told us he'd rescue everyone,\nand not to worry.
You gotta be kiddin' me. Just when I was\nthinkin' the kid mighta grown a tiny bit of\nsense without any power to rely on...
He is such a hopeless idiot!
Um... Is everything okay? We're worried\nthat he might be doing something\nreckless on our account.
Can't deny it. But hey, no need to worry.\nHe and I ain't so weak as to get done in\nby that buncha goons.
I gotta make sure he understands that\ntoo...
*huff* *pant* Looks like I managed\nto give them the slip.
I can't defeat all the Syndicate soldiers\nsolo, so I've gotta help the villagers and\nget out of here fast.
You're the prototype wyrmbound soldier.\nOr the failed prototype, I should say.
Hey, I'm askin' you what happened to your\nBarbatos B-Unit.
You mean Lil' Barb? Who knows.\nI don't have to tell you anyway.
Huh. Well, if he's around, then hurry up\nand call him so you two can merge.
You sure about that? If I use my\nwyrmbinding, I'll be able to totally wreck\nyou and make it home in time for lunch.
Yeah, that's right. And I hope you do.\nNow come on, hurry up and merge with\nyour B-Unit.
(Bluffing's not working...but there are no\nother soldiers around here. Surely I can\ntake just this one guy on my own...right?)
He not coming? Fine, then I'll go ahead\nand use my own wyrmbinding first.\nCome forth, Barbatos B-Unit!
What?! Lil' Barb?! No, wait, that's—
Correct. This ain't YOUR Barbatos\nB-Unit. This is MY Barbatos B-Unit.
Ha ha ha! Witness my power! I'm no\nfailure like you. I am a TRUE wyrmbound\nsoldier!
HA HA HA! POWER! SO MUCH POWER!
Well? Come on. Now it's your turn.\nI'm ITCHING to test this out and see just\nhow much power I'm working with here!
Urgh... What a mess. Dammit.\nAt this rate, I'm toast...
HEY! Why aren't you using wyrmbinding?!\nOr are you just unable to? Freakin' boring.
BORING, BORING! If you can't even make a\ngood test subject, then just die in the dirt\nlike the worm you are!
Was that...Lil' Barb? It can't be.\nHe...protected me? No way...
Shut UP, man.\nYou're givin' me a headache.
Right as rain, kid. An attack like\nthat ain't gonna do crap to me.
Don't believe me, huh? Just take\na gander. Ain't a scratch on me.
You're right! Oh, what a relief.\nI'm so glad you're okay, Lil' Barb!
But this means you get it now, right?\nI ain't so soft that I need you actin'\nlike my human meat shield.

You're a bonehead, but a damned
impressive guy. You look about as reliable
as a hedgehog in a balloon factory, but I
get the feelin' you could survive anything.
I believe that you'll be all right, even if I\ndon't lose my mind worryin' about each\nand every little thing ya do.
Now what about me?\nAm I nothing special?\nDo I look super weak to you?
No! That's not true at all! You ARE\nimpressive. Without you, I'm totally\npowerless!
Then believe in me. I'm made of sturdier\nstuff than you think. I ain't gonna burden\nyou with survivor's guilt, ya hear me?
From now on, BELIEVE in me,\nyou knucklehead!
Yeah... I will. I'm sorry for everything,\nLil' Barb. I was so, so wrong.
...Appreciate it.\nNow let's whoop this fool, Farren!
Finally ready to tussle, are we?
You're a real stand-up guy,\nwaitin' for us to use wyrmbinding.
I waited because stepping on insects\nis boring. Now make sure you struggle\nenough to make this fun for me!
Right! Don't worry, his attacks barely\neven tickle. Just use me to stop 'em!
Cocky, aren't we? Fine. I'll give you a\nlittle taste and you can see for yourself!
...Heh. See? Told ya. I've had worse\npillow fights. Ya see that, pal?! I ain't\ngot a scratch on me!
Rrrgh... You're nothing but a failure!\nFine, how about THIS?!
*pant* *huff* How about that, you\nmiserable failure? This is the power\nof a TRUE wyrmbound soldier...
For ＂true power,＂ it kinda sucks, guy.
Ridiculous... Did I peg him wrong?

Sorry, bud. Right now, the kid and I are
loaded with so much power, I'm surprised
it ain't comin' out our eyeballs. And on that
note, Farren—it's our turn now!
Damn right it is. I can feel the power\nwelling up from deep inside me!
Your strength is mine, kid. When you didn't\nbelieve in me, you couldn't unleash our\nfull might.
I get it now... THIS is OUR true power!\nCome on, Lil' Barb!
Looks like nobody from the Syndicate's\nnippin' at our heels. I think we made it.
Yeah. I'm so relieved.\n...Oh, by the way, Lil' Barb?
Thanks for showing up. You saved me.
So, er... Ahem. Anyway. If you learned\nfrom all this, then think ahead a little\nbefore you act next time.
I will. But even if something like this\nhappens again, you'll come for me, right?
D-don't get ahead of yourself.\nI can't be your babysitter.
Tsk. Somebody needs his mouth washed\nout with soap. But...I know you've got my\nback. Right, partner?
No way! I ain't gettin' mixed up in any\nmore of your crazy plans to save everyone\nyou run into!
Come ooon, don't say that. Helping\npeople and seeing them smile is nice,\nisn't it? Don't you think so?
You're askin' the wrong guy. I'm just sayin',\nthis is the last time I babysit you.
